for several years , bariatric surgery has proven to be effective for the treatment of type 2 diabetes , but the basic research was carried out among people with morbid obesity , having a body mass index ( BMI ) of 35 or higher .
BMI , a measure of weight relative to height , is considered normal at value from 18.5 to 24.9 .
a BMI of 25 or above indicates that a person is overweight , and people with a BMI above 30 are considered obese .
you can calculate your BMI here : 1.usa.gov/1d0zqdv .
for the new study , researchers from the Taiwan hospital min Sheng general used data collected since 2007 , to compare two types of bariatric surgery - gastric bypass and sleeve gastrectomy , with the medical treatment of type 2 diabetes in people with obesity .
the average BMI of those who have undergone surgery , fell from 31 to 24.5 by the end of the fifth year of their participation in the study .
at the same time , the BMI of those who received non-surgical treatment for diabetes , remains roughly at the level of 29 .
among those who had surgery , completely cured of diabetes by 36 % , and partially - 28 % .
in the group that received medical treatment , for comparison , a complete cure for diabetes was observed only 1 % , and partial - only about 2 % .
in addition , indicators of blood pressure , high triglycerides and `` bad '' LDL cholesterol `` as a whole were better in the surgical group , '' the authors said .
the researchers also controlled the A1s hemoglobin levels in the blood , which reflect the blood sugar levels in the dynamics .
hemoglobin A1c test is better to keep below 7 percent , `` the researchers write .
after surgery , the average level of hemoglobin A1C test decreased from roughly 9 % to approximately 6 % .
in the therapeutic group , however , it has remained stable , at around 8 % .
but the best indicators of glycemic control , reflecting good levels of hemoglobin A1C test , not reduced the mortality rate in five years , according to the study by Dr. Su Chi Cheng and colleagues .
the research team also compare the average results of two types of surgical treatment .
for the fifth year , compared with the group , Polc sleeve gastrectomy , shunt group lost more weight ( 18.7 kg versus 14.2 kg ) , achieved a greater reduction in BMI ( 7.4 vs. 5.1 ) and hemoglobin A1s ( 3.1 % versus 2.1 % ) , and was closer to a complete remission of diabetes ( 46.9 % versus 16.7 % ) .
although the new study does not demonstrate the advantages of surgical methods in terms of life expectancy after five years , there is confirmation of the results of the study of people with excess body weight in Sweden that surgical treatment actually leads to increased life expectancy , according to Blackstone from the University College of Medicine in Phoenix , Arizona .
according to the Swedish research for people with obesity , bariatric intervention , the likelihood of dying for 15 years was approximately 29 % lower compared with the group , which uses a more traditional methods .
