Xi Jinping calls to make the economy more open to the world
the economy needs to become more open to the whole world to spur its growth , as President Xi Jinping said on Tuesday in a speech to the group facing the task of leadership reforms .
`` China should focus on attracting foreign investors and experts and to develop a policy of openness , '' he said , referring to the participants of the 16th meeting of the Committee of the central leading group for comprehensively deepening reforms .
according to him , the expansion of openness and deepening reforms will give the economy a boost and vitality and will provide a new space for economic development .
the leading group adopted a number of directives , including the introduction of regulation investor access to the market , changing the rules of border controls , the promotion of state-owned enterprises ( SOE ) , attracting private capital and a review of the registration system .
according to the statement , will be compiled a list of sectors of the economy and production , inaccessible for investment .
the system will be gradually debugged through trial programs .
this is an important step because it will give the market a bigger role in allocating resources , ensuring the legitimacy of the business sector and increasing openness , as said in the statement .
the government will also weaken the control of the powers granted to them to companies , ensuring that the companies themselves will conduct their business .
the statement also says that China will allow border regions to develop new models of cross-border economic cooperation and new mechanisms to strengthen local growth .
even more areas will be available for private investors in order to increase the openness of state-controlled sectors of the economy .
`` The government will not change its policy toward foreign investors and will defend the legitimate interests of companies with foreign funding , as well as provide them with the best conditions , '' it said in a statement .
additionally will facilitate the procedure for submitting applications for permanent residence permits for foreigners , or `` green card '' by optimizing the requirements and simplifying the process of filing .
the meeting also discussed ensuring the rights of lawyers and questions of professional training of judges and prosecutors .
according to an official report issued after the meeting , it was also attended by Prime Minister Li Keqiang and Liu Yunshan and Zhang Gaoli ministers .
